Task 1B – Technical Design Plan

1. Overview of the Technical Solution

What to write about
	•	Briefly explain what your final product will be (website, app, system etc.)
	•	Describe how users will interact with it
	•	Mention the main features your solution will include
	•	Explain how it solves the problem from Task 1A

Example points
	•	The system will be a responsive website
	•	Users can navigate using a menu
	•	It will allow users to perform specific tasks (login, search, view content etc.)

Tip 💡
Keep it simple. Think of this section like “what the system will do overall.”

⸻

2. User Interface Design

What to write about
	•	Explain your wireframes
	•	Describe the layout of each main page
	•	Explain why you placed elements where you did
	•	Mention usability and accessibility considerations

Things to mention
	•	Navigation bar
	•	Buttons and menus
	•	Page layout
	•	Mobile responsiveness
	•	Accessibility (clear fonts, colours, readable layout)

Tip 💡
When talking about a wireframe, use phrases like:
“This layout was chosen to make navigation simple for the user.”

⸻

3. User Journey / Workflows

What to write about
	•	Explain the workflows you created
	•	Describe the steps the user takes to complete tasks
	•	Explain how the system responds to user actions

Example structure
	•	User opens homepage
	•	User selects an option
	•	System processes request
	•	User receives output

Tip 💡
Always explain why the workflow is efficient or easy for users.

⸻

4. System Architecture / How the System Works

What to write about
	•	Describe the technical structure
	•	Frontend vs backend (if relevant)
	•	How information flows through the system

Possible things to mention
	•	Web server
	•	Browser
	•	Database
	•	APIs (if used)

Tip 💡
Even a simple explanation works:
“The frontend will display the interface while the backend processes user requests.”

⸻

5. Data Handling and Storage

What to write about
	•	What data the system collects
	•	Where it is stored
	•	How it is processed

Examples
	•	User information
	•	Form submissions
	•	Stored content

You can also mention:
	•	Databases
	•	Tables
	•	Data validation

Tip 💡
Always mention security of user data if relevant.

⸻

6. Security Considerations

What to write about
	•	How the system protects users and data
	•	Measures to prevent misuse

Examples
	•	Secure login systems
	•	Input validation
	•	HTTPS
	•	Password protection
	•	Limiting access to data

Tip 💡
Examiners love seeing awareness of security risks.

⸻

7. Accessibility Considerations

What to write about
Explain how the design works for all users, including people with disabilities.

Examples:
	•	Clear fonts
	•	Good colour contrast
	•	Keyboard navigation
	•	Screen reader compatibility
	•	Simple navigation

Tip 💡
Mention WCAG accessibility principles if you want extra marks.

⸻

8. Testing Plan

What to write about
Explain how the system will be tested to make sure it works.

Examples:
	•	Functional testing
	•	User testing
	•	Checking links and navigation
	•	Testing on different devices

Tip 💡
Mention testing before release and fixing bugs.

⸻

9. Tools and Technologies

What to write about
List and explain the technologies used.

Examples:
	•	HTML
	•	CSS
	•	JavaScript
	•	Frameworks
	•	Design tools (Figma, Adobe XD etc.)

Explain why you chose them.

Tip 💡
Link tools to benefits like performance, flexibility, or ease of development.

⸻

Final Tip for Task 1B

The examiners mainly want to see that you can justify design decisions.

Try to use sentences like:
	•	“This was chosen because…”
	•	“This improves usability by…”
	•	“This ensures security because…”
